                                    </extent>
                                    <condition>Paper stained throughout with some effect on legibility, e.g. <locus from="5" to="6" scheme="pages"/>. <locus from="1" to="1" scheme="pages"/>: dark and stained, which indicates the manuscript may have been stored without binding for some time. In the corners there are holes with rust stains, which partially bleeds through to <locus from="7" to="7" scheme="pages"/>. Edges trimmed, with some loss of marignal additions. <locus from="40" to="190" scheme="pages"/>: holes from bookworms. Leaves repaired and strengthened with paper strips in places, e.g. <locus from="2" to="2" scheme="pages"/> and <locus from="23" to="23" scheme="pages"/>.</condition>
